mysql vs sqlserver vs postgresql: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=loZ5L_NmCG8 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VSJ3SA_z4Gk
1. Change Column Size in SQL Server: ALTER TABLE Employee ALTER COLUMN FirstName VARCHAR(50);
2. Change the size in the Oracle database: ALTER TABLE Employee MODIFY (FirstName VARCHAR2(50));
3. change the size in the PostgreSQL database: ALTER TABLE Employee ALTER COLUMN FirstName TYPE VARCHAR(50);
